## purpose
Defines the canonical architectural role of builder in CivilizationOS.

## design_intent
Builder is the bounded execution structure
for creating,
placing,
configuring,
assembling,
or instantiating governed objects and environments.

Builder is not merely a UI convenience.
It is the formal path by which design intent
becomes structured reality
within world, nation, organization, housing, market,
and other dependent domains.

## architectural_position
Builder sits between:
- design intent
- configuration intent
- placement/construction intent
- validation and policy gates
- resulting domain objects

## required_behavior
- build intent must remain explicit
- source template/configuration basis must remain explicit
- actor authority must remain explicit
- placement or construction boundary must remain explicit
- current build state and historical build state must remain distinguishable

## canonical_rules
- builder must not invent authority
- builder output must remain attributable
- template/config source must remain explicit
- failed build must not masquerade as completed build
- ambiguous build boundary fails closed

## state_model
The builder domain distinguishes:
- draft build
- validated build
- approved build
- executing build
- failed build
- completed build
- historical build

## actor_boundary
- builder owner
- builder operator
- reviewer
- approver
- adapter

## decision_matrix
- if template/config basis is missing, stop build
- if actor authority is unclear, fail closed
- if target boundary is invalid, deny execution
- if build fails, preserve failure trace
- if build completes, preserve attributable completion trace

## review_checklist
- build intent is explicit
- template/config basis is explicit
- execution boundary is explicit
- lifecycle is explicit
